<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245015>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Pelionella kansui Kaydan, sp. nov., holotype. Note: each cluster on dorsum with 1 – 5 (usually 2) multilocular disc pores; absence of quinquelocular pores on venter; few marginal cerarii; large circulus; multilocular disc pores in compact band on dorsum of abdominal segment VII." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245015/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

